conditionDetails: Fallen Trees - 13 large crossings of Jeremy's Run. Going up back to the car, crossings #2, 3 and 7 have to be crossed 10 to 20 ft above the trail line. crossing #2 was deep to my waist (I am 5'9")... if you do not have poles I would not recommend as the water strength was significant. I'd qualify these as dangerous crossings for kids. the yellow trail and blue trail had significant overgrowth, and the blue trail had a fair amount of stinging nettle! A great run!

summary: A relatively short jaunt to a mesa overlooking the Visitor Center.

name: Pine Creek Waterfall Trail

name: Cable Mountain Trail
summary: A straightforward, rolling mesa trail culminating at a historic viewpoint.

name: Deertrap Mountain Trail
summary: A relatively short journey to a rarely visited viewpoint.

name: Hop Valley Trail
summary: Wander above, then through one of Zion's beautiful valleys.

name: Chinle Trail

name: Margarita
summary: A part of a great trail system over lots of slickrock with great views and fun terrain.

name: East Rim Trail

name: Lime
summary: A fun trail of primarily slick rock.

name: Holy Guacamole
summary: Hiking along the Zion National Park boundary doesn't get much better than this.

name: Wire Mesa Loop

name: Kolob Arch Trail

name: JEM Trail

name: Cryptobionic

name: South Rim Trail

name: White Trail

conditionDetails: Dry - recorded section is Hidden Canyon trail.

name: Windmill Trail

name: Practice Trail
summary: A good warm up before hitting the main trails

name: Bowls and Ledges
summary: A fun connector and warm up for the other trails.

name: Goosebump
summary: A "roller coaster" of a trail.
